==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ombre
<hw>Om"bre</hw>}</mhw> <pr>(?)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>hombre</ets>, fr. Sp. <ets>hombre</ets>,
lit., a man, fr. L. <ets>homo</ets>. See <er>Human</er>.]</ety> <def>A
game at cards, borrowed from the Spaniards, and usually played by three
persons.</def> <rj><au>Pope.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>When <qex>ombre</qex> calls, his hand and heart are free,⟦br⟧
And, joined to two, he fails not to make three.</q>
<rj><qau>Young.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ombre</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Ombre
<hw>Om"bre</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., of uncertain origin.]</ety>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A large Mediterranean food fish (<spn>Umbrina
cirrhosa</spn>): -- called also <altname>umbra</altname>, and
<altname>umbrine</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ombrometer</ent>⟦br⟧
